item.content:encoded:
Association of civil engineering students (ACES) organized an interactive event named “DOORWAY TO ACES”. It was conducted on 2nd February 2022. The event was conducted on Google Meet. On the first day of the event, all the participants were called to introduce themselves and share their hobbies, goals and etc so that it will reduce their public speaking fears. They also got a golden opportunity to interact with their respective seniors and teachers. Students found this event very helpful and useful as they got more to know about ACES and their branch. On the second day of the event interview session held where we select the active members for ACES. There were 64 online registrations with a total of 64 students participating in this event.

Below are the details of the event: –

DATE: 25th January 2022

The first-day ‘INTERACTION PROGRAMME’ was broken into 3 parts: –

●      Part 1- Interaction Programme from 11:00 AM to 11:30 AM

●      Part 2- Come to know about ACES from 11:30 AM to 12:15 PM

●      Part 3- Questioning and answering from 12:15 PM to 12:30 PM

●      Participants: – 64

Date: 2nd February 2022

The second-day’ DOORWAY TO ACES’ held from 3:30 PM to 5:00 PM.

●      Participants: – 46

item.content:encoded:
In this situation of pandemic Association of Civil Engineering Students (ACES) organized a webinar (web seminar) on Github. The webinar was conducted on 27th September 2020 and started at 11 P.M. on Sunday. The event was conducted on the Zoom platform. The speaker for the same was Amanjot Singh (CSE department) and Tandeep Singh (Ex M.Tech). Guest of Honor Dr. H.S Rai, H.O.D of Civil Engineering Department at GNDEC shared his prized words with the participants, motivating them and telling them the importance of Github. The event was started off by ACES faculty advisor Yuvraj Singh and Aman Mittal (Discipline Head) and was passed onto the speakers. Both the speakers shared their views on Github and tried to clear all the doubts of the participants. The webinar had 11

0 participants and all participated in the public poll.
At last, the link for the feedback form was shared with the participants to get their valuable comments.
